CEREMONY
The ceremony was something we‚Äôve been dreaming of for a long time. Along with the help of our wedding planners, we put in a lot of thought designing what exactly we wanted for this monumental moment and it came together even better than we had imagined. The ceremony location was at one of the highest points on the Epoch property which overlooks miles of wine country in Paso Robles. The colors surrounding us at this time of year are exactly why we love the Fall season so much. In an effort to provide shade and intimacy we installed a wooden truss system and semi sheer white draping, to create a relaxing and partially shaded ceremony location. White florals and lush greenery trailed up the columns of the wooden
structure and down the ceremony aisle. Beautiful white floral blooms surrounded us on a circle riser stage. As guests arrived by shuttle, they were invited to take a walk through the vineyard to the ceremony site. Our pastor and dear friend Judah Smith officiated the ceremony. It couldn‚Äôt have been more perfect. We exchanged hand written vows in front of the people we love most. Looking around and seeing the faces of each and every single person there, really put into perspective what is most important in life. Love. The sun set just as we said our ‚ÄúI Do‚Äôs‚Äù and the most beautiful pink sky was our backdrop as we walked back down the aisle as Mr. and Mrs. Taylor Lautner for the first time.
